    <item>
      <title>Salesforce Bulk API 2.0 Integration with Apache Camel</title>
      <link>https://sedatgoc.com/blog/salesforce-bulkapi2-integration-with-apache-camel/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 22:58:00 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://sedatgoc.com/blog/salesforce-bulkapi2-integration-with-apache-camel/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Why I am writing this blog?&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;why-i-am-writing-this-blog&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#why-i-am-writing-this-blog&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img&#xA;    class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xA;    loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;    decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;    fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;Salesforce Bulk API 2.0 Connectivity with Apache Camel&#34;&#xA;    width=&#34;1383&#34;&#xA;    height=&#34;850&#34;&#xA;    src=&#34;https://sedatgoc.com/blog-content/salesforce-bulkapi2-integration-with-apache-camel/apache-camel-salesforcebulkapi2-diagram_hu_a480bd2a77ddaa75.png&#34;&#xA;    srcset=&#34;https://sedatgoc.com/blog-content/salesforce-bulkapi2-integration-with-apache-camel/apache-camel-salesforcebulkapi2-diagram_hu_a480bd2a77ddaa75.png 800w, https://sedatgoc.com/blog-content/salesforce-bulkapi2-integration-with-apache-camel/apache-camel-salesforcebulkapi2-diagram_hu_253d0bf6d69d6411.png 1280w&#34;&#xA;    sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xA;    data-zoom-src=&#34;https://sedatgoc.com/blog-content/salesforce-bulkapi2-integration-with-apache-camel/apache-camel-salesforcebulkapi2-diagram.png&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;Salesforce Bulk API 2.0 Connectivity with Apache Camel&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I have seen many integration projects with Salesforce. In several Salesforce integration projects I have observed that batch lifecycle management is often poorly implemented. I want to show how to upload bulk data to Salesforce via Apache Camel Salesforce component, how to handle errors and failed jobs because most of the integrations does not have proper error handling.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>OPC UA Connectivity with Apache Camel and Apache PLC4X</title>
      <link>https://sedatgoc.com/blog/apache-camel-opcua-connectivity-wtih-plc4x/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 15 Feb 2026 19:07:25 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://sedatgoc.com/blog/apache-camel-opcua-connectivity-wtih-plc4x/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;What is OPC UA and Why Should We Care?&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;what-is-opc-ua-and-why-should-we-care&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-opc-ua-and-why-should-we-care&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img&#xA;    class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xA;    loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;    decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;    fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;OPC UA and Apache Camel Integration Architecture&#34;&#xA;    width=&#34;872&#34;&#xA;    height=&#34;362&#34;&#xA;    src=&#34;https://sedatgoc.com/blog-content/opcua-apache-camel-connectivity-content/architecture-diagram_hu_c49d62004559c767.png&#34;&#xA;    srcset=&#34;https://sedatgoc.com/blog-content/opcua-apache-camel-connectivity-content/architecture-diagram_hu_c49d62004559c767.png 800w, https://sedatgoc.com/blog-content/opcua-apache-camel-connectivity-content/architecture-diagram.png 1280w&#34;&#xA;    sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xA;    data-zoom-src=&#34;https://sedatgoc.com/blog-content/opcua-apache-camel-connectivity-content/architecture-diagram.png&#34;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;High-level architecture of data flow from PLCs to Enterprise Systems via Apache Camel.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Have you ever heard of OPC UA? Although I have been working with integration layers for many years, I had never heard of this technology until last year. To summarize about OPC UA, we can say basically it&amp;rsquo;s a standardized, secure and semantic data exchange protocol for machines, PLCs and sensors. Most manufacturers use this protocol in their PLCs and sensors. Of course, industrial systems can communicate using other protocols like Modbus, S7, ADS etc.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
